3 Question: Are any ADL’s and Conditions somehow associated ?

3.1 χ2χ2 tests for independence

  • If p-value is <0.05 (ADL and Condition are dependent), there is an assocation between ADL and Condition.
  • If p-value is >0.05 (ADL and Condition are independent), no assocation between ADL and Condition.

Note:

The reduced version of the contingency table aggregates

  • No and Only with help in category No.
  • Yes, with much difficulty, Yes, without much difficulty and Yes, with some difficulty in category Yes.

4 Clustering techniques

Cluster analysis or clustering is the task of grouping a set of objects in such a way that objects in the same group (called a cluster) are more similar (in some sense or another) to each other than to those in other clusters.

4.1 Hierarchical clustering

plot clusters

4.2 K-means

k-means clustering aims to partition nn observations into kk clusters in which each observation belongs to the cluster with the nearest mean, serving as a prototype of the cluster.
